track_notes: Park at the Eagle Lake parking lot and follow the horse trails to the ridge of EV4.  Follow the ridge until you are above the tree line at which point you can either continue the ridge line or drop to avoid the exposure of the ridge.  If you are solo, avoiding the exposed ridge may be your best option but it entails a difficult scree side hill and lots of elevation loss.  Choose your poison.  There are three places where you will loose significant elevation only to have to reclaim it again on worse terrain.  Cell phone reception at the summit is sketchy and intermittent.

This route is a scramblers route and has been graded SC6, YDS3.  The south ridge has the most scrambling moves and is probably the most technically challenging.  Many obstacles can be bypassed with difficulty but following the spine of the ridges usually turns out to be the easiest route.
